1 Email Integration			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for sending project exports (SVG Gantt charts, Team Planner snapshots, resource utilisation graphs) as email attachments via SMTP with KeePass credential management.	information	1.1	PO-EMAIL-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
6.1 Email Integration Requirements			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall send emails via SMTP with authentication using credentials retrieved from a KeePass database entry.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-EMAIL-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall support SMTP with STARTTLS on a configurable port (default 587), falling back to unencrypted SMTP when TLS is not available.	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-EMAIL-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall store configuration settings (SMTP server, SMTP port, use TLS flag, sender address, KeePass entry name) via the SettingsManager under the email/ prefix in QSettings.	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-EMAIL-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall expose an is_configured() function that returns True when server, sender address, and KeePass entry name are all set, and False otherwise.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-EMAIL-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall expose a test_connection() function that connects to the SMTP server, authenticates with the KeePass credentials, and returns a tuple (success: bool, error_message: str).	functional requirement	1.1.5	PO-EMAIL-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall expose a send_email(to, subject, body, attachments) function that supports single or multiple recipients, plain text body, and optional file attachments as a list of (filename, bytes) tuples.	functional requirement	1.1.6	PO-EMAIL-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall provide an Email Configuration dialog accessible from a button in the Report ribbon panel (always enabled, as email settings are global and not project-gated).	functional requirement	1.1.7	PO-EMAIL-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Configuration dialog shall display the KeePass database lock state with three states: not configured, locked, and unlocked (with entry list populated).	functional requirement	1.1.8	PO-EMAIL-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Configuration dialog shall include a Test Connection button that saves current settings, calls email_integration.test_connection(), and displays the result in a QMessageBox.	functional requirement	1.1.9	PO-EMAIL-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Configuration dialog shall include a Send Test Email button that opens a wider dialog (400 px) prompting for a recipient email address, with a Use My Email button that auto-fills the recipient by looking up the current KeePass entry username in Active Directory.	functional requirement	1.1.10	PO-EMAIL-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Configuration dialog (EmailConfigDialog) shall include a "From KeePass…" button in the Sender (Per-Project) section that auto-fills the sender email address by looking up the current KeePass entry username in Active Directory; the button shall be absent from the EmailServerEditDialog.	functional requirement	1.1.11	PO-EMAIL-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall use a configurable SMTP connection timeout of 30 seconds.	functional requirement	1.1.12	PO-EMAIL-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall track the last send result (timestamp, success, recipient count, error message) and last test result (timestamp, success, error message) in module-level variables for diagnostic purposes.	functional requirement	1.1.13	PO-EMAIL-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email integration shall expose a get_config_summary() function that returns a dict with configured, smtp_server, smtp_port, smtp_use_tls, sender_address, keepass_entry_set (bool), last_send, and last_test keys, without exposing any passwords or sensitive credentials.	functional requirement	1.1.14	PO-EMAIL-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Sensitive information (SMTP passwords, KeePass credentials) shall never be written to log files, debug dumps, QSettings, or displayed in error messages.	functional requirement	1.1.15	PO-EMAIL-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All email integration error messages shall be user-friendly and shall not contain technical jargon, stack traces, or exception class names.	functional requirement	1.1.16	PO-EMAIL-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When no SMTP email accounts are configured (SettingsManager.get_email_configs() returns an empty list) or no active account name matches any configured account, the email export actions in the Report ribbon split-button popups — Email Gantt SVG, Email to All Resources, and Email Timeline SVG — shall be rendered as disabled (greyed-out, non-interactive); each disabled item shall show a tooltip explaining how to add an SMTP account and select it via Email Config. The enabled/disabled state shall be re-evaluated at application startup and whenever the Email Accounts dialog (EmailServersDialog) or the Email Config dialog (EmailConfigDialog) is closed.	functional requirement	1.1.17	PO-EMAIL-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
6.2 Email Multiple Account Requirements			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall support storing multiple named SMTP email account configurations (name, smtp_server, smtp_port, smtp_use_tls) as a JSON array in a plain file (email_configs.json) next to the executable; sender_address and the KeePass credential entry are NOT stored per account and are NOT included in this file.	functional requirement	1.2.1	PO-EMAIL-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall designate one email configuration as the active account, stored by name in the email_configs.json file under the active_config_name key.	functional requirement	1.2.2	PO-EMAIL-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On first access, if the email/configs list is empty but the legacy single-config key email/smtp_server is set, the system shall automatically migrate the existing settings into a config entry named "Default" and store it in the email/configs list.	functional requirement	1.2.3	PO-EMAIL-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall provide an Email Accounts dialog (EmailServersDialog) accessible from an always-enabled "Email Accounts" button in the Report ribbon panel that lists all configured SMTP accounts and supports Add, Edit, Delete, Set Active, Move Up, and Move Down operations.	functional requirement	1.2.4	PO-EMAIL-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Accounts list shall display each account as "name ★ — server", with a ★ suffix appended to the active account name.	functional requirement	1.2.5	PO-EMAIL-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall provide an Email Account Edit dialog (EmailServerEditDialog) for adding or editing a single SMTP configuration, containing fields for Name, SMTP Server, SMTP Port, and Use TLS checkbox only; the dialog shall NOT contain a Sender Address field, a KeePass section, or a "From KeePass…" button — sender address is stored per-project in enterprise custom properties, not per account.	functional requirement	1.2.6	PO-EMAIL-023.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Email Account Edit dialog (EmailServerEditDialog) shall NOT include a Test Connection button; the dialog is limited to SMTP server configuration fields only.	functional requirement	1.2.7	PO-EMAIL-024.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All email_integration module functions (is_configured, send_email, test_connection) shall accept an optional config dict parameter; when provided, the explicit config is used in place of the active account.	functional requirement	1.2.8	PO-EMAIL-025.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When no explicit config is provided, email functions shall resolve the active config via SettingsManager.get_active_email_config(); when that returns no valid dict (e.g. empty list), functions shall fall back to the legacy single-config QSettings keys for backward compatibility.	functional requirement	1.2.9	PO-EMAIL-026.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The get_config_summary() function shall include multi-config keys num_configs (int), active_config_name (str), active_configured (bool), and configs (list of dicts with keepass_entry_set bool instead of the raw entry name) alongside the existing legacy keys.	functional requirement	1.2.10	PO-EMAIL-027.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The KeePass credential entry for email authentication shall be stored globally under the email/keepass_entry QSettings key and shall be shared by all SMTP accounts; it shall be configurable only via the Email Configuration dialog (EmailConfigDialog), not per individual account.	functional requirement	1.2.11	PO-EMAIL-028.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The _get_keepass_entry(config) function shall resolve the KeePass entry using a two-step fallback: first, if the config dict contains a non-empty keepass_entry key (present in legacy-migrated "Default" entries for backward compatibility), that value is returned; otherwise, the global email/keepass_entry value from SettingsManager is returned.	functional requirement	1.2.12	PO-EMAIL-029.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The is_configured(config) function shall return True only when smtp_server, sender_address, and the resolved KeePass entry (via the two-step fallback in _get_keepass_entry) are all non-empty; a config dict without a keepass_entry key shall be considered fully configured when the global email/keepass_entry is set.	functional requirement	1.2.13	PO-EMAIL-030.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
6.3 Email Config JSON File Storage Requirements			1.3	1_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall store the email account list (configs array) and active account name in a plain JSON file named email_configs.json; the file format shall be { "active_config_name": str, "configs": [ ... ] } with UTF-8 encoding and human-readable 2-space indentation.	functional requirement	1.3.1	PO-EMAIL-031.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When running as a bundled PyInstaller executable (sys.frozen is True), email_configs.json shall be placed in the same directory as the executable so that the entire installation folder can be copied between machines to transfer the configuration.	functional requirement	1.3.2	PO-EMAIL-032.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When running in development mode (sys.frozen is absent or False), email_configs.json shall be placed at the project root directory (one level above src/).	functional requirement	1.3.3	PO-EMAIL-033.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On the first call to SettingsManager.get_email_configs() when email_configs.json is absent or empty, the system shall migrate existing data from QSettings in priority order: (1) new-style email/configs JSON string, (2) legacy single-config keys (email/smtp_server, etc.); after migration the data shall be written to email_configs.json so subsequent calls read from the file only.	functional requirement	1.3.4	PO-EMAIL-034.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Legacy single-config migration shall produce a config entry named "Default" containing only smtp_server, smtp_port, and smtp_use_tls; the keepass_entry QSettings value and sender_address shall NOT be copied into the per-account dict, since sender_address is now stored per-project.	functional requirement	1.3.5	PO-EMAIL-035.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The KeePass credential entry name (email/keepass_entry) shall remain in QSettings and shall NOT be written to email_configs.json, since it references a machine-local KeePass database path and is not portable.	functional requirement	1.3.6	PO-EMAIL-036.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Reading email_configs.json shall be fault-tolerant: a missing file, invalid JSON, or OS error shall return an empty dict without raising an exception, causing the caller to fall back to migration or return an empty list.	functional requirement	1.3.7	PO-EMAIL-037.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email_configs.json file shall be excluded from version control (listed in .gitignore) because it contains machine-specific server hostnames and sender addresses.	functional requirement	1.3.8	PO-EMAIL-038.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
6.4 Email Account Selection and Per-Project Sender Name			1.4	1_4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The redesigned EmailConfigDialog shall provide an account-selection section containing: a QComboBox listing all configured SMTP accounts by name (one item per account), a "Manage Accounts…" button, and a warning label informing the user that no SMTP accounts are configured; the combo shall be shown and the label hidden when the account list is non-empty, and the label shall be shown and the combo hidden when the list is empty.	functional requirement	1.4.1	PO-EMAIL-039.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The EmailConfigDialog "Manage Accounts…" button shall open the EmailServersDialog; after that dialog closes the account QComboBox shall be reloaded from SettingsManager.get_email_configs() and the previously selected account name re-selected when still present in the refreshed list.	functional requirement	1.4.2	PO-EMAIL-040.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The EmailConfigDialog shall include a per-project Sender Name QLineEdit for the display name used in the From: header of outgoing emails (e.g. "Alice Smith"); this field is separate from the Sender Address (smtp-level From address) that is also stored per-project in enterprise custom properties, not per SMTP account.	functional requirement	1.4.3	PO-EMAIL-041.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On accepting the EmailConfigDialog, the selected SMTP account name shall be written to the project sidecar JSON under the MPXJ enterprise custom property key "Email Active Account" using a java.util.HashMap passed to project.getProjectProperties().setCustomProperties(), using the same persistence mechanism as JiraSyncConfigDialog.	functional requirement	1.4.4	PO-EMAIL-042.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On accepting the EmailConfigDialog, the sender display name shall be written to the project sidecar JSON under the MPXJ enterprise custom property key "Email Sender Name" using the same HashMap mechanism.	functional requirement	1.4.5	PO-EMAIL-043.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When EmailConfigDialog is initialised with a project argument, it shall load the active account name from the "Email Active Account" custom property (falling back to SettingsManager.get_active_email_config_name() when absent) and pre-select the matching combo item; it shall also load the sender display name from the "Email Sender Name" custom property and pre-fill the Sender Name field.	functional requirement	1.4.6	PO-EMAIL-044.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The MainWindow.open_email_config() method shall retrieve the current project via logic.get_data() and pass it to EmailConfigDialog; when the dialog is accepted and a project is open, _mark_dirty() shall be called so the updated custom properties are persisted on the next file save.	functional requirement	1.4.7	PO-EMAIL-045.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	EmailConfigDialog._get_current_config() shall return the selected account dict with both a "sender_address" key injected from the Sender Address field and a "sender_name" key injected from the Sender Name field (each injected only when non-empty) when the account combo contains at least one entry; it shall return None when the combo is hidden (no accounts configured); the hidden/visible check shall use QWidget.isHidden() rather than isVisible() to work correctly in test environments where the dialog top-level window is not shown.	functional requirement	1.4.8	PO-EMAIL-046.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The email_integration._get_sender_address() function shall return the sender address formatted as "Display Name <address>" (RFC 2822 name-addr, produced via email.utils.formataddr) when the resolved config dict contains a non-empty "sender_name" value; when "sender_name" is absent or an empty string the plain email address shall be returned unchanged.	functional requirement	1.4.9	PO-EMAIL-047.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The EmailConfigDialog "Sender (Per-Project)" group box shall contain, in order: a Sender Address QLineEdit (smtp-level From: address, e.g. "alice@example.com"), a "From KeePass…" button that auto-fills the Sender Address by performing an Active Directory lookup on the current KeePass entry username, and a Sender Name QLineEdit (display name for the From: header, e.g. "Alice Smith").	functional requirement	1.4.10	PO-EMAIL-048.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On accepting the EmailConfigDialog, the sender email address shall be written to the project sidecar JSON under the MPXJ enterprise custom property key "Email Sender Address" using the same java.util.HashMap mechanism as the other per-project keys ("Email Active Account", "Email Sender Name").	functional requirement	1.4.11	PO-EMAIL-049.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When EmailConfigDialog is initialised with a project argument, it shall load the sender email address from the "Email Sender Address" enterprise custom property and pre-fill the Sender Address field; when the property is absent or empty the field shall remain blank.	functional requirement	1.4.12	PO-EMAIL-050.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
